, to name only a few, interviews with Catherine Robbe-Grillet and Eileen Myles, English and Russian fairy tales, and articles on the history of feminist film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanadian poetryy21st century. 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh  a1920.  a1920s.  aAlberta.  aCanadian literature.  aavante garde.  aavante-garde.  acento.  acollage.  acut and paste.  acut-up poem.  aexperimental poetry.  ahistory.  amurder poetry.  amurder trial.  areal crime.  atrial narrative.  atrue crime.  awoman murderer.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773850696?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773850696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773850696/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles